                    "company": "University of Amsterdam",
                    "description": "My PhD project entails a political ethnographic study of the situated practices of Financial Intelligence Units (FIUs) in Europe. I aim to understand the way in which financial intelligence is made commensurable across national borders, how financial knowledge is enacted on a daily level and how situated judgement manifests in practice. The goal of my project is to unpack and bring to the fore the perspectives of security professionals; the daily dilemma\u2019s they face in terms of societal expectations, privacy considerations, technological restrictions, and other practice-related challenges.\n\nThe PhD is part of the project 'FOLLOW: Following the Money from Transaction to Trial,' led by Prof. Marieke de Goede (UvA) and funded by the European Research Council. FOLLOW studies the path of the suspicious financial transaction across private and public spheres through the analysis of how knowledge is formed and mobilized by banks, FIUs and courts. FOLLOW is interested in the everyday life of security practices and the complex dilemmas faced by the actors at stake, and relies on participant observation coupled with in-depth semi-structured interviews.",
